# Security Audit
## Objective
Review IT scopes and goals, identify risk, evaluate controls, and report improvements

## Skills Practiced 
- Risk Assessment
- Security Controls
- Security Policies
- Compliance
- Documentation
- Analytical Thinking

## Tools
- Google doc checklist
- Google Cybersecurity Certificate program

## What I learned
In this objective, I learned that organizations evaluate security postures by reviewing assets, assessing the risks in the company, reporting, and recommending improvements needed to secure valuable data. I also gained a lot of experience by reviewing documents and going through a checklist of what assets and compliance needed to be improved.
## Key Takeaways 
- Security audits help identify and point out weaknesses before any disaster happens.
- Policies and security controls reduce organizational risks.
- Documentation of assets is essential for identifying weaknesses in cybersecurity.

## Status
Completed as part of the Google Cybersecurity Certificate program.

## Reflection
I learned that cybersecurity is not just about using Python, Linux, and SQL. Organizations also rely on monitoring, physical security measures like locks and guards, documentation of assets, policies, and risk management to protect sensitive data and systems. 
